129
00:08:54,918 --> 00:08:56,099
Finding our voice in socials.

130
00:08:58,995 --> 00:09:02,957
So when I started at Ponkel, I didn't really have a clue what I was doing.

131
00:09:03,357 --> 00:09:06,919
Um, to be honest, I didn't know how to use Twitter properly.

132
00:09:06,939 --> 00:09:08,419
I didn't know how to use discord.

133
00:09:08,819 --> 00:09:13,402
So I had to learn those and work out the best way to use each of those platforms.

134
00:09:14,462 --> 00:09:18,904
I made sure I varied the content that I was posting, um, such as game updates

135
00:09:19,004 --> 00:09:25,327
and polls, um, any, yeah, any bug fixes and all of that kind of thing, um, just

136
00:09:25,968 --> 00:09:27,408
to reach all different people.

137
00:09:28,485 --> 00:09:31,307
And over my time posting over the last year,

138
00:09:31,347 --> 00:09:33,228
I've really worked out what does well

139
00:09:33,548 --> 00:09:36,310
and what doesn't do so well for our posts.

140
00:09:36,330 --> 00:09:37,691
So things that get high engagement

141
00:09:38,031 --> 00:09:39,912
are anything such as big game updates

142
00:09:40,793 --> 00:09:43,355
and interacting with the players

143
00:09:43,415 --> 00:09:44,936
and asking them for their feedback

144
00:09:44,996 --> 00:09:46,517
and what they're enjoying the most

145
00:09:46,877 --> 00:09:48,918
and how many achievements they've got,

146
00:09:49,759 --> 00:09:51,520
if they've 100%ed the game or not.

147
00:09:52,461 --> 00:09:55,323
And the low engagement posts are anything such as

148
00:09:55,945 --> 00:09:59,486
Fan art, unfortunately, and just smaller game updates,

149
00:09:59,707 --> 00:10:00,327
little patches.

150
00:10:02,048 --> 00:10:03,368
I like to try and jump on trends,

151
00:10:03,808 --> 00:10:06,530
but I'm very selective about what trends we jump on.

152
00:10:07,950 --> 00:10:12,072
It's great for visibility and reaching new audiences,

153
00:10:12,253 --> 00:10:14,714
but you want to make sure that you don't

154
00:10:15,414 --> 00:10:16,555
jump on every single trend.

155
00:10:17,615 --> 00:10:19,796
Just choose the ones that fit your brand the best.

156
00:10:20,877 --> 00:10:22,998
I try and use the trending hashtags as well,

157
00:10:23,058 --> 00:10:23,918
just to get you.

158
00:10:25,204 --> 00:10:29,525
to reach new audiences and get better visibility for our posts.

159
00:10:30,626 --> 00:10:32,566
In summary, you've got to be agile.

160
00:10:32,926 --> 00:10:36,467
Study what works and make sure you're looking at your analytics.

161
00:10:37,647 --> 00:10:43,309
For example, for Vampire Survivors, I realized that the players really love Garlic, Flaw

162
00:10:43,329 --> 00:10:46,450
Chicken and our character Poe Racho, who is a stinky old man.

163
00:10:47,604 --> 00:10:50,885
And any post about them, just, they love it.

164
00:10:51,065 --> 00:10:54,726
They love to share it and yeah, it's really fun.

165
00:10:57,507 --> 00:11:00,207
Consistency and timing is really important.

166
00:11:00,827 --> 00:11:03,928
So as I mentioned before, we did the teasers

167
00:11:04,068 --> 00:11:05,489
leading up to the 1.0 launch,

168
00:11:06,129 --> 00:11:07,689
where we posted every single day.

169
00:11:07,709 --> 00:11:10,590
I realized that 4 p.m. is a really good time

170
00:11:10,630 --> 00:11:13,791
for us to post, as we reach people in the UK

171
00:11:13,951 --> 00:11:17,032
and in America, so it gets better visibility.

172
00:11:20,932 --> 00:11:27,675
Once I discovered what kind of tone of voice worked with our audience and the kind of branding

173
00:11:27,795 --> 00:11:31,197
for Pongal and Vampire Survivors, it was a really big turning point for me.

174
00:11:31,477 --> 00:11:35,679
Because to start off with, as I said I wasn't that experienced, I thought I had to be really

175
00:11:35,759 --> 00:11:41,582
serious on social and just post about game updates and bugs and keep it really serious.

176
00:11:41,782 --> 00:11:44,703
But as soon as I started relaxing and

177
00:11:45,524 --> 00:11:48,965
writing more friendly posts like the one you see there, just a bit more fun.

178
00:11:49,545 --> 00:11:53,927
They started doing a lot better and they're a lot more shareable and got a lot better engagement.

179
00:11:55,928 --> 00:12:00,550
It was important for me to pay attention to the player likes and dislikes as mentioned before,

180
00:12:00,650 --> 00:12:07,974
so they really like garlic and floor chicken, whereas things like the character reskins,

181
00:12:08,274 --> 00:12:09,975
all that kind of stuff doesn't really do as well.

182
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:18,789
If you're hiring a community manager, it's really important to trust them.

183
00:12:19,229 --> 00:12:25,074
Give them space to experiment with different types of posts, to jump on trends,

184
00:12:25,454 --> 00:12:29,257
and also to kind of create their own guidelines.

185
00:12:29,277 --> 00:12:31,099
So, what I mean by this is...

186
00:12:33,942 --> 00:12:35,803
Like they've got to look after their own mental health.

187
00:12:36,123 --> 00:12:40,063
So not responding to really negative hate comments

188
00:12:40,203 --> 00:12:43,084
and all of that is, it makes a big difference,

189
00:12:43,144 --> 00:12:44,604
like if you don't make them respond to those.

190
00:12:45,284 --> 00:12:46,684
So personally, I just ignore those

191
00:12:47,505 --> 00:12:50,265
and also set boundaries such as people,

192
00:12:51,345 --> 00:12:54,046
when you get messages asking constantly for new platforms,

193
00:12:55,226 --> 00:12:56,766
it's a lot of work to respond to all of those.

194
00:12:57,526 --> 00:12:59,987
And yeah, personally I ignore those

195
00:13:00,107 --> 00:13:01,707
because I don't want to say the wrong thing

196
00:13:01,767 --> 00:13:02,827
and give people the wrong impression.

197
00:13:12,183 --> 00:13:15,485
So I find that one of the things that Pongal does best is acknowledge players.

198
00:13:16,366 --> 00:13:21,849
In our Discord we get a lot of feedback and we're always making sure that our players

199
00:13:21,929 --> 00:13:23,170
know that they're listened to.

200
00:13:24,130 --> 00:13:29,873
So we respond to all types of feedback, positive, negative, and any bug reports.

